          <styled-content style="color:#2A9A57;font-size:15px;background-color:#cccccc">taxon_name </styled-content>
          <styled-content style="font-size:15px;background-color:#cccccc">= </styled-content>
          <styled-content style="color:#936EB8;font-size:15px;background-color:#cccccc">"Umbra limi"</styled-content>
          <styled-content style="font-size:15px;background-color:#cccccc">٫ </styled-content>
          <styled-content style="color:#2A9A57;font-size:15px;background-color:#cccccc">                       seqrange </styled-content>
          <styled-content style="font-size:15px;background-color:#cccccc">= </styled-content>
          <styled-content style="color:#936EB8;font-size:15px;background-color:#cccccc">"1:2000"</styled-content>
          <styled-content style="font-size:15px;background-color:#cccccc">٫       </styled-content>
          <styled-content style="color:#2A9A57;font-size:15px;background-color:#cccccc">                       getrelated </styled-content>
          <styled-content style="font-size:15px;background-color:#cccccc">= </styled-content>
          <styled-content style="color:#7F1B56;font-size:15px;background-color:#cccccc">FALSE</styled-content>
          <styled-content style="font-size:15px;background-color:#cccccc">)        </styled-content>
        </preformat>
      </p>
      <p>Then one can ask if ’RAG1’ exists in any of the gene names.</p>
      <p>
        <preformat>
          <styled-content style="font-size:15px;background-color:#cccccc">out[</styled-content>
          <styled-content style="color:#7F1B56;font-size:15px;background-color:#cccccc">grep</styled-content>
